Bradley Schmidt wrote:
> Interesting question, Greg. In my experience disconnecting the breather
> introduces a massive vacuum leak into the FI system. This would lean it so
> much it would not run. At the very least there would be a huge difference in
> the idle speed.
> 
>  
> 
> I would suggest pulling the breather and the hose, pulling it off the
> s-boot. I wonder if there is some kind of blockage in this setup?? If there
> was it would answer why you have excess crankcase pressure and also why
> pulling the breather doesn't kill the FI... IIRC it's a straight run from
> the breather on top of the case to the S-boot, with a metal male-male insert
> that plugs in the s-boot and into the hose...
